From: CHEN Xuan <chenxuan@iscas.ac.cn>
Subject: [PATCH] version the shared libraries

magma installs libmagma and libmagma_sparse unversioned. Give them a
SONAME/version (driven by the -DMAGMA_SO_VERSION cache variable) so the
unversioned .so symlink can live in the -devel sub-package while the
versioned library stays in the main runtime package.

Upstream request: https://bitbucket.org/icl/magma/issues/77/versioning-so
diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 405b2725f..7cd30e0d8 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -612,6 +612,11 @@ foreach( TEST ${sparse_testing_all} )
 endforeach()
 add_custom_target( sparse-testing DEPENDS ${sparse-testing} )
 
+# openRuyi: give the shared libraries a SONAME/version so the runtime
+# and devel sub-packages can be split (upstream ships them unversioned).
+set_target_properties( magma PROPERTIES VERSION ${MAGMA_SO_VERSION} SOVERSION ${MAGMA_SO_VERSION} )
+set_target_properties( magma_sparse PROPERTIES VERSION ${MAGMA_SO_VERSION} SOVERSION ${MAGMA_SO_VERSION} )
+
 
 # ----------------------------------------
 # what to install
